Sec. 13.027. STANDARD NET WEIGHT OR COUNT SET BY RULE. (a)
The department by rule may establish a standard net weight or net
count for any commodity and prescribe tolerances for those standards
as the department considers necessary for the proper protection of
the public.
(b) A person violates this chapter if the person fails or
refuses to comply with the rules adopted under this section.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1025, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.
Amended by:
Acts 2013, 83rd Leg., R.S., Ch. 924 (H.B. 1494), Sec. 3.05, eff.
September 1, 2013.

